<CRANTaskView>

  <name>gR</name>
  <topic>gRaphical models in R</topic>
  <maintainer email="sorenh@agrsci.dk">Soren Hojsgaard</maintainer>
  <version>2005-04-25</version>
  
  <info>
    A graphical model is a class of statistical models that can be
    represented by a mathematical graph which in turn can be used to
    identify conditional independence properties. This task view is a
    collection of packages intended to supply R code to deal with
    graphical models. If you think that some package is missing from the
    list, please notify me.
    
    The packages can be roughly structured into the following topics:
    <ul>
      <li><i>Representation of graphs</i>: <pkg>mathgraph</pkg>
          implements matrix representations of graphs and provide a plot function.
          <!-- <pkg>giRaph</pkg> is an S4 implementation of 4 common
          representations of graphs--></li>
      <li><i>Display and interaction</i>: <pkg>dynamicGraph</pkg>
          uses Tcl/Tk (cross-platform) to provide an advanced graphical user
	  interface for display and interaction with graphs. The package is
	  used as front-end to other graphical model packages.</li>
      <li><i>"Classical" Models</i>: <pkg>gRbase</pkg> sets up (meta) data
          representation and suggests a way to implement models and fitting
          engines -- illustrated by hierarchical log-linear models;
          <pkg>CoCo</pkg> is an advanced suite of functions for
          contingency tabels (and much more); <pkg>mimR</pkg> provides an
	  interface to MIM (Mixed Interaction Models) and only runs on Windows;
	  <pkg>SIN</pkg> provides model selection of Gaussian graphical Markov models;
	  <pkg>ggm</pkg> fitting graphical Gaussian models.</li>
      <li><i>Bayesian networks</i>: <pkg>deal</pkg> is a package for learning
          Bayesian networks.</li>
      <li><i>BUGS models</i>: The following packages adds functions to
          support the BUGS and JAGS programs: <pkg>bayesmix</pkg>, <pkg>boa</pkg>,
	  <pkg>coda</pkg>, <pkg>rbugs</pkg>, <pkg>R2WinBUGS</pkg>.</li>
    </ul>
  </info>

